nodes.documentation:
@notice `_newVote` starts a new vote and adds it to the votes array.
        votes are not started with a vote from the caller, as candidates
        and candidate weights need to be supplied.
@param _executionScript The script that will be executed when
       this vote closes. Script is of the following form:
           [ specId (uint32: 4 bytes) ] many calls with this structure ->
           [ to (address: 20 bytes) ]
           [calldataLength (uint32: 4 bytes) ]
           [ function hash (uint32: 4 bytes) ]
           [ calldata (calldataLength bytes) ]
       In order to work with a dot vote the execution script must contain
       Arrays as its first six parameters. Non-string array lengths must all equal candidateLength
       The first Array is generally a list of identifiers (address)
       The second array will be composed of support value (uint256).
       The third array will be end index for each candidates Information within the infoString (optional uint256)
       The fourth array is a string of concatenated candidate information, the infoString (optional string)
       The fifth array is used for description params (optional string)
       The sixth array is an array of identification keys (optional uint256)
       The seventh array is a second array of identification keys, usually mapping to a second level (optional uint256)
       The eigth parameter is used as the identifier for this vote. (uint256)
       See ExecutionTarget.sol in the test folder for an example  forwarded function (setSignal)
@param _metadata The metadata or vote information attached to the vote.
@return voteId The ID(or index) of this vote in the votes array.

addCandidate(uint256,string,address,byte.details: `addCandidate` allows the `ROLE_ADD_CANDIDATES` to add candidates     (aka voting options) to an open dot vote.

params._description: This is the address that will be displayed along the       option when voting
params._eId1: External ID 1, can be used for basic candidate information
params._eId2: External ID 2, can be used for basic candidate information
params._metadata: Any additional information about the candidate.       Base implementation does not use this parameter.
params._voteId: id for vote structure this 'ballot action' is connected to

allowRecoverability(address).details: By default deriving from AragonApp makes it recoverable

params.token: Token address that would be recovered

allowRecoverability(address).return: bool whether the app allows the recovery

params._voteId: id for vote structure this 'ballot action' is connected to

canExecute(uint256).return: True if the vote is elligible for execution.

params._sender: Address of the entity trying to forward

canPerform(address,bytes32,uint256[]).details: Check whether an action can be performed by a sender for a particular role on this app
canPerform(address,bytes32,uint256[]).return: Boolean indicating whether the sender has the permissions to perform the action.        Always returns false if the app hasn't been initialized yet.

params._voteId: The ID of the Vote on which the vote would be cast.
params._voter: The address of the entity trying to vote

canVote(uint256,address).return: True is `_voter` has a vote token balance and vote is open

params._candidateIndex: The candidate descrciption of the candidate.
params._voteId: id for vote structure this 'ballot action' is connected to
The ID of the Vote struct in the `votes` array

getInitializationBlock().return: Block number in which the contract was initialized

params._actionId: id for action structure this 'ballot action' is connected to
params._optionIndex: The option descrciption of the option.

params._actionId: The ID of the Action struct in the `actions` array

getRecoveryVault().details: Get the recovery vault for the app
getRecoveryVault().return: Recovery vault address for the app

params._voteId: The ID of the Vote struct in the `votes` array
The ID of the Vote struct in the `votes` array
The ID of the Vote struct in the `votes` array.
params._voter: The voter whose weights will be returned

hasInitialized().return: Whether the contract has been initialized by the time of the current block

params._candidateSupportPct: Percentage of votes cast that must       support a voting option for it to be valid (expressed as a 10^18       percentage, (eg 10^16 = 1%, 10^18 = 100%)
params._minQuorum: Percentage of voters that must participate in       a dot vote for it to succeed (expressed as a 10^18 percentage,       (eg 10^16 = 1%, 10^18 = 100%)
params._token: MiniMeToken address that will be used as governance token
params._voteTime: Seconds that a vote will be open for tokenholders to       vote (unless it is impossible for the fate of the vote to change)

params._executionScript: EVM script to be executed on approval

newVote(bytes,string).return: voteId Id for newly created vote

params._minQuorum: Percentage of voters that must participate in a vote for it       to be considered valid (expressed as a 10^18 percentage, e.g. 10^16 = 1%,       10^18 = 100%)

params._globalCandidateSupportPct: Percentage of votes cast that must support       a voting option for it to be valid (expressed as a 10^18 percentage,       e.g. 10^16 = 1%, 10^18 = 100%)

params._token: Token balance to be sent to recovery vault.

params._supports: Array of support weights in order of their order in                 `votes[_voteId].candidateKeys`, sum of all supports                 must be less than `token.balance[msg.sender]`.
params._voteId: id for vote structure this 'ballot action' is connected to

addCandidate(uint256,string,address,byte.notice: Add voting option "`_description`" to dot vote #`_voteId` for the purpose of `_metadata`.

canExecute(uint256).notice: `canExecute` is used to check that the participation has been met        and the vote has reached it's end before the execute function is        called.

canForward(address,bytes).notice: Used to ensure that the permissions are being handled properly        for the dot vote forwarding

canVote(uint256,address).notice: `canVote` is used to check whether an address is elligible to        cast a dot vote in a given dot vote action.

forward(bytes).notice: Creates a vote to execute the desired action

getCandidate(uint256,uint256).notice: `getCandidate` serves as a basic getter using the description        to return the struct data.

getCandidateLength(uint256).notice: `getCandidateLength` returns the total number of voting options for        a given dot vote.

getOption(uint256,uint256).notice: `getOption` serves as a basic getter using the description        to return the struct data.

getOptionLength(uint256).notice: `getOptionLength` returns the total number of options for        a given action.

getVote(uint256).notice: `getVote` splits all of the data elements out of a vote        struct and returns the individual values.

getVoteMetadata(uint256).notice: `getVoteMetadata` returns the vote metadata for a given dot vote.

getVoterState(uint256,address).notice: `getVoterState` returns the voting power for a given voter.

initialize(address,uint256,uint256,uint6.notice: Initializes DotVoting app with `_token.symbol(): string` for        governance, minimum quorum of        `(_minQuorum - _minQuorum % 10^14)        / 10^16`, minimal candidate acceptance of        `(_candidateSupportPct - _candidateSupportPct % 10^14) / 10^16`        and vote duations of `(_voteTime - _voteTime % 86400) / 86400`        day `_voteTime >= 172800 ? 's' : ''`

isForwarder().notice: `isForwarder` is a basic helper function used to determine        if a function implements the IForwarder interface

newVote(bytes,string).notice: Create a new dot vote for "`_metadata`".

setGlobalQuorum(uint256).notice: Global parameter change: A dot vote will require a minimum participation from `@formatPct(_minQuorum)`% of the total token supply for the proposal to be considered valid.

setglobalCandidateSupportPct(uint256).notice: Global parameter change: A dot voting option will require at least `@formatPct(_globalCandidateSupportPct)`% of the votes for it to be considered valid.

transferToVault(address).notice: Send funds to recovery Vault. This contract should never receive funds,        but in case it does, this function allows one to recover them.
